Plenty of languages provide filenames/line numbers in assertions without using macros.<p>Furthermore, `__LINE__` and `__FILE__` style macros are a pretty safe subset of macros that aren&#x27;t really representative of the problems with macros. Compare:<p><pre><code>    #include <stdlib.h>
    #include <stdio.h>
    #include &quot;my_macro_library.h&quot;

    int main()
    {
        int x = 0;
        printf(&quot;%i&quot;, increment(x));

        printf(&quot;%i&quot;, __LINE__);

        return EXIT_SUCCESS;
    }

</code></pre>
There are a ton of different implementations of an `increment` macro which are going to cause undefined behavior here. Contrast with the `__LINE__` macro: it&#x27;s implemented by the compiler and has unsurprising, well-defined behavior.

